originalText.text:
Sales dude was hella rude. Chatting on the phone when I walked in. After leisurely wrapping up his phone conversation he gave me a head nod that I assume meant "How can I help you?" Lo and behold he speaks no English and is all slow nods and lackadaisical gestures.

Sewing machine pedal seemed a little pricey. And they don't take credit cards. So I'm just supposed to walk around with $300+ in cash if I had wanted to buy a sewing machine? Come the eff on, y'all.

Go in case of emergency, otherwise skip it.
